item.title: Dungeoneering leeching?
item.dc:creator: @Rawr_lol Rawr lol
item.description:
@Rawr_lol wrote:

Phaze One:

300m+

Maybe even more than that…

When I used to sell floors we charged 1.5m for floor 1-19 2m for floor 20-35 36+ for 2.6m.

You’d be wasting money to leech before you can reach floor 30 (in my opinion).

My rough calculations of leeching 59-99 (start leeching at 59 if you can handle regular dg’ing until that level) would be 375,600,000.

It could be a lot higher if you choose a leech clan that charges more than that.

item.title: Dungeoneering leeching?
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

[quote=“Kidpaparoach, post:21, topic:449971”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=552868.msg4054831#msg4054831 date=1342836106]

You don’t get why people let level 3s leach for free o.o, but nvm lol.

What?

He’s saying they let level 3’s leach for free at times because it drops monster levels down for them and you have high skill stats to open sometimes un-accessible doors
[/quote]
thanks, couldn’t be bothered explaining what I meant[/quote]

I knew what you meant, I just didn’t understand your logic.

Although level 3s lower the combat level of the NPCs, skill doors are based off the players’ skills and many times, if a skiller leecher has very high skills, higher than those of the other teammates, the skiller would have to open the door. Not only is that an inconvenience (for the skiller to teleport to the ggs), but the team would also have to clear the room of any NPCs or hazards before the skiller could teleport there, thus wasting a lot of time. That’s why people don’t like it when level 3s leech.

So yeah, it’s because of skillers that there may be un-accessible doors, and also a door may require 103 strength just because a skiller has 99 herblore, which wastes a lot of time (making the potion etc).

Sorry for any mistakes in my explanation, in a rush atm.

item.title: Dungeoneering leeching?
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

depends on the floor. You really dont want to pay for larges until floor 30 or even 36. At 36 you are getting approximately 40k exp. in the warped floors at level 94 or so ive heard you can get 170k exp. So just presume that it scales linearly and figure out how many floors there are inbetween 36 and whatever floor at 94. That will give you your average exp per floor then divide exp to 99 by that and times that by 2m. Floor 36 is 71? So estimate from 1m exp, or 12m exp to go.
